text: was a town located in Ōchi District, Shimane Prefecture, Japan. As of 2003, the town had an estimated population of 3,437 and a density of 31.22 persons per km2. The total area was 110.10 km2. On October 1, 2004, Sakurae was merged into the expanded city of Gōtsu. Category:Dissolved municipalities of Shimane Prefecture
title: Sakurae, Shimane
